watched.title: Delivering success at the Leaders’ Summit on Climate
watched.copy: The summit could stoke a collective sense that finally – after decades of negotiations – this is the pivotal year for climate. The US is back at the climate table, and the Biden-Harris Administration is making climate action a center organising principle of its government.

watched.copy: Solar panels could be the latest get rich quick scheme for landowners. Or they could leave many investors out of pocket. Tom Heap asks if this solar gold rush is sustainable.
